author: Duncan Lindsay For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Lee Carter returns in EastEnders but what happens now? | Metro News
text:
Duncan Lindsay for Metro.co.uk Thursday 16 Feb 2017 8:27 pm (Picture: BBC) 
EastEnders fans had thought that they had seen the last of Lee Carter when he abandoned his wife Whitney and left her a note claiming that he didn’t love her anymore. But in the closing moments of the most recent visit to Walford, Lee got in touch with his worried dad Mick in order to arrange a meeting. 
With another chapter of Lee’s story still to play out, what will the pair have to say to each other when they come face to face – and is there a hopeful ending in store for the troubled character? Or will everything come to a close in an even more bleak way than before? 
Mick had been anxiously waiting for Lee to contact him so when he finally did, there was definite relief. But there is still a lot to sort out – not least of all Lee’s marriage to Whitney. Will Mick persuade him to come home and talk everything through properly with his heartbroken wife? 
Whatever happens, there are emotional scenes ahead… 
EastEnders continues on Friday 17th February on BBC One at 8pm.
